adult means anyone who has reached 19 years of age and, for all
purposes incidental to an application under section 6 (2), includes a person who has reached 18
years of age;

bcl:paragraph.bcl:text:
suffering from an illness, disease or injury that results in the adult dealing
              with his or her financial affairs in a manner that is likely to cause substantial
              damage or loss in respect of those financial affairs;

all adults are entitled to live in the manner they wish and to accept or refuse
            support, assistance or protection as long as they do not harm others and they are
            capable of making decisions about those matters;

all adults should receive the most effective, but the least restrictive and
            intrusive, form of support, assistance or protection when they are unable to care for
            themselves or their financial affairs;

enter, without a court order or a warrant, any premises where the adult may be
              located and use any reasonable force that may be necessary in the
